pattern_2.text: I was suspecting that the study may be about different colors on certain skin tones that may make one appear slimmer or heavier. I was also suspecting that perhaps it could be about being led to believe one is slimmer or heavier after immediately being presented after a variety of opposite stimuli (e.g., one could look slimmer if presented after a whole onslaught of heavier people). I believe too that darker skinned players were in red uniforms while lighter skinned players were in green and yellow uniforms.
